FORMER Kaizer Chiefs and Mpumalanga Black Aces star, Abia Nale (30), is off the market.&nbsp; The star from Sebokeng, in the Vaal, south of Jozi, tied the knot to the love of his life, Constance Radebe in a private ceremony at the Koinonea Bible Church in Zone 14, Sebokeng.&nbsp; The service was conducted by Bishop Isaac Mthimkulu.&nbsp; The couple exchanged vows in a service that was attended by family members and a few close friends.&nbsp; Sources close to the couple told Sunday Sun the footballer tried to keep the nuptials under wraps.&nbsp; &ldquo;The ceremony was private because Abia didn&rsquo;t want the media to know about it.&nbsp; &ldquo;He has been keeping it secret since early this year, when he started hinting that he was planning to marry his lover. He doesn&rsquo;t like people knowing about his private life,&rdquo; the insider explained.&nbsp; The source further claimed some of the family members were not told about the wedding.&nbsp; &ldquo;That&rsquo;s how secret the wedding was,&rdquo; said the source.&nbsp; Sunday Sun sources say a date for the white wedding is yet to be confirmed.&nbsp; But another source told the People&rsquo;s Paper that a white wedding was expected soon.&nbsp; The source told the SunTeam Abia was serious about Constance and that they had been together for a while.&nbsp; When asked for comment, Abia said he didn&rsquo;t want to discuss his private life in the media.&nbsp; Constance could not be reached for comment.&nbsp;